title: For Sale:  Absolutely beautiful 1910-ish Iver Johnson's Champion single 16
postcontent:
This example of an early Iver Johnson's Champion Single 16 gauge shotgun is not your ol' "truck" gun. The original bluing is perfect on the barrel and the original reddish tone on the action is also perfect. The serial number 8303 makes it... damn old. The number on the fore stock matches the serial number on the bottom of the trigger guard. It sat untouched in my dear departed dad's gun case for forty years. 
I refinished the furniture with dark walnut stain and 11 hand rubbed and sanded coats of poly. It's like looking in a mirror and it feels REAL good. This isn't the finish that was used on the original piece but it is a heck of a lot more durable.
The only new part is a correct reproduction Iver Johnson butt plate. I will include the banged up original piece and a second spare. There is a small slice of wood that had broken off from the top of the grip next to the tang sometime in the last century. (see bottom photo). I sanded the area down and continued with the refinishing.
This old shotgun was COMPLETELY dismantled, cleaned, lubed and reassembled. Lock up is real tight. 
Comes with two full boxes of new modern Federal Game Shok, 1165 fps, 2 3/4", #6 16 gauge shells. This old shotgun may need lower velocity shells.
$250.00. For sale only. I am not entertaining trades.   
Save the low ball offer. I have a fireplace that this would look good sitting over. 
If interested, shoot a reply. Meet up in Bellevue, Redmond or Kirkland.

An anti-gun bill that will criminalize the private transfer of handguns and certain semi-automatic rifles at gun shows will likely be heard this week or next in the House Rules Committee.  House File 285, introduced by state Representative John Lesch (DFL-66B), passed in the House Public Safety, Finance and Policy Committee by a 10 to 8 vote on April 8 after being amended to include a ban on private sales.  If HF 285 passes in the House Rules Committee, it will be eligible for final consideration on the House floor as early as this week.

This type of legislation is dangerous and must be stopped, as this scheme is the first step towards criminalizing ALL private transfers and can only be enforced with gun registration.  And, as we know from experiences in California, Australia and Great Britain, gun registration enables gun confiscation — only from honest citizens — since criminals do not register their guns or submit to criminal investigations. title: For Sale:  don't waste your time with CLARK Corner in El Dorado

This is the sequence of events detailing my experience with Clark Corner:
I called to see if they could re-barrel a rifle for me.
They said they could, so I brought it in.  He said it would be about 3 weeks.
I called 4 weeks later and he said he had not started it.
I called 2 weeks later and he said he wasn't going to do it.
I came and got my rifle back.

I would suggest not wasting any time with Clark Corner.  Beyond the waste of time described above, getting someone to answer the phone or even someone being at the shop when it is supposed to be open was risky at best.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Modified Original Xbox w/ Loads of Installed Games + Extras
postcontent:
Looking to sell my fun little toy; a modified original Xbox (i.e. NOT AN XBOX 360). It has a different operating system on it alongside the standard Xbox OS, so not only can you use it as a normal Xbox and play games from disk, but it has some extra features that make it pretty sweet. The original Xbox harddrive has been replaced by what I believe is a 300gb IDE PC harddrive, giving this thing a ton of storage. On top of that, you can even connect it via an FTP server to access videos, pictures, music, etc. that is stored on your computer on the Xbox, making this thing essentially a media PC along with being a gaming console. The real bread & butter of this, however, is the fact that it has a TON of games preinstalled on the Xbox itself that can be played just like a normal Xbox game. I will include a list of all the games on the bottom of this post, it is ridiculous. On top of that, it has a couple different emulators on it that I have never really played around with. It comes with the console itself, one power cable, one RCA (red/yellow/white) cable, and one Logitech wireless controller w/ the dongle for the console. I am honestly not in a hurry to sell this, since it's got a lot of awesome games on it and honestly is pretty rare to find these days, since finding the modchips and whatnot to do this is pretty difficult. title: For Sale:  Magtech 9mm FMJ (.34 Cents / Round before TAX)
postcontent:
I don't work for West Coast Armory nor do I want to freely advertise for them, but I'm tired of the gouger here Armslist.

Seriously, go to either West Coast Armory in Everett or Bellevue and get yourself 4 boxes of Magtech 9mm 50 rounds at 16.99 each. Last time I check they allow you to take 4 boxes per day. That's 200 rounds. 

Math:
$16.99 + tax = $18.60 per box of 50 (.37/round)

50 Rounds  = $18.60 
100 Rounds  = $37.20
200 Rounds  = $74.40
500 Rounds  = $186
1000 Rounds = $372

See? Compare these prices with the gougers. They are charging 300 bucks for 500 rounds? Unbelievable. 

I ask all of you please do the following.
1. List up on Armslist the prices you've seen at your local gun shops the price of ammo and please keep updating it. Put the Price/Round on the title so we can compare.
2. Flag the gougers.
3. Keep America Free.
